  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients implanted with an implantable cardioverter defibrillators for primary
             prevention of ischemic heart disease with ejection fraction of the left ventricle ≤
             35%

          -  Ejection fraction of the left ventricle ≤ 35%

          -  Age ≥ 18 years

          -  Patients with disorders of the ventricular heart rate recorded by the implantable
             cardioverter defibrillators and not older than 2 years

          -  Implantable cardioverter defibrillators patient carrier for at least 3 years.

          -  Lack of disorders of ventricular heart rate in the memories of the implantable
             cardioverter defibrillators in the last three years prior to study entry

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patient electro-driven,

          -  Patients with cardiac disease other qu'ischémique,

          -  Manifest impossibility of a collection of stationary signal Finapres: Atrial
             fibrillation, many premature, unsuccessful execution of verticalization,

          -  Important metabolic disorders such as ketoacidosis or dyskaliémie (&lt;3.5 or&gt; 5 mmol /
             L)

          -  Age &lt;18 years
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
